hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

iterator.name: iterator
iterator.comment: Returns an Iterator that iterates over this Iterable object.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of elements in this.

Counting all elements may be involve running through all elements and can therefore be slow.

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no element in this collection.

isNotEmpty.name: isNotEmpty
isNotEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is at least one element in this collection.

first.name: first
first.comment:
Returns the first element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError. Otherwise this method is equivalent to this.elementAt(0)

last.name: last
last.comment:
Returns the last element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError.

single.name: single
single.comment:
Returns the single element in this.

If this is empty or has more than one element throws a dart-core.StateError.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

map.name: map
map.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable where each element e of this is replaced by the result of f(e).

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.map.f will not be invoked. The transformed elements will not be cached. Iterating multiple times over the the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.map.f multiple times on the same element.

where.name: where
where.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable with all elements that satisfy the predicate restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.where.test.

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.where.test will not be invoked. Iterating will not cache results, and thus iterating multiple times over the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.where.test multiple times on the same element.

expand.name: expand
expand.comment:
Expands each element of this dart-core.Iterable into zero or more elements.

The resulting Iterable runs through the elements returned by restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.expand.f for each element of this, in order.

The returned dart-core.Iterable is lazy, and calls restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.expand.f for each element of this every time it's iterated.

contains.name: contains
contains.comment: Returns true if the collection contains an element equal to restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.contains.element.

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment: Applies the function restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.forEach.f to each element of this collection.

reduce.name: reduce
reduce.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining elements of the collection using the provided function.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.reduce((value, element) => value + element);

fold.name: fold
fold.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining each element of the collection with an existing value using the provided function.

Use restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.fold.initialValue as the initial value, and the function restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.fold.combine to create a new value from the previous one and an element.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.fold(0, (prev, element) => prev + element);

every.name: every
every.comment: Returns true if every elements of this collection satisify the predicate restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.every.test. Returns false otherwise.

join.name: join
join.comment:
Converts each element to a dart-core.String and concatenates the strings.

Converts each element to a dart-core.String by calling restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.toString on it. Then concatenates the strings, optionally separated by the restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.join.separator string.

any.name: any
any.comment: Returns true if one element of this collection satisfies the predicate restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.any.test. Returns false otherwise.

toList.name: toList
toList.comment:
Creates a dart-core.List containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

The elements are in iteration order. The list is fixed-length if restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.toList.growable is false.

toSet.name: toSet
toSet.comment: Creates a dart-core.Set containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

take.name: take
take.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable with at most restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.take.n elements.

The returned dart-core.Iterable may contain fewer than restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.take.n elements, if this contains fewer than restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.take.n elements.

It is an error if restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.take.n is negative.

takeWhile.name: takeWhile
takeWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that stops once restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.takeWhile.test is not satisfied anymore.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable starts iterating over the elements of this.

When the iterator encounters an element e that does not satisfy restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.takeWhile.test, it discards e and moves into the finished state. That is, it does not get or provide any more elements.

skip.name: skip
skip.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips the first restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.skip.n elements.

If this has fewer than restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.skip.n elements, then the resulting Iterable is empty.

It is an error if restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.skip.n is negative.

skipWhile.name: skipWhile
skipWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips elements while restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.skipWhile.test is satisfied.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable iterates over all elements of this.

As long as the iterator's elements satisfy restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.skipWhile.test they are discarded. Once an element does not satisfy the restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.skipWhile.test the iterator stops testing and uses every later element unconditionally. That is, the elements of the returned Iterable are the elements of this starting from the first element that does not satisfy restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.skipWhile.test.

firstWhere.name: firstWhere
firstWhere.comment:
Returns the first element that satisfies the given predicate restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.firstWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.firstWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.firstWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

lastWhere.name: lastWhere
lastWhere.comment:
Returns the last element that satisfies the given predicate restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.lastWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.lastWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.lastWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

singleWhere.name: singleWhere
singleWhere.comment: Returns the single element that satisfies restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.singleWhere.test. If no or more than one element match then a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

elementAt.name: elementAt
elementAt.comment:
Returns the restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.elementAt.indexth element.

The restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.elementAt.index must be non-negative and less than restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.length.

Note: if this does not have a deterministic iteration order then the function may simply return any element without any iteration if there are at least restlib_server/server.ForwardingSequence.elementAt.index elements in this.
